question:
District category contains High-rise Apartment Complex, Academic District, and Landmark District.
Supermarkets category contains Peapod, Vons, Metro (Canada), and Grocery Outlet.
Product category contains Trail Mix, Yogurt, Sports Drinks, and Canned Peaches.
The number of each Academic District 's Vons equals the difference of each Peapod 's Product and each Vons 's Yogurt.
The number of each Metro (Canada) 's Yogurt equals 10.
The number of each High-rise Apartment Complex 's Peapod equals the difference of each Peapod 's Product and each Landmark District 's Peapod.
The number of each Peapod 's Yogurt equals 3.
The number of each High-rise Apartment Complex 's Metro (Canada) equals 13 times each Landmark District 's Product.
The number of each Vons 's Yogurt equals each Grocery Outlet 's Yogurt.
The number of each Grocery Outlet 's Yogurt equals 13.
The number of each Landmark District 's Peapod equals each Peapod 's Yogurt.
How many Supermarkets does High-rise Apartment Complex have?
solution:
Define each Peapod 's Yogurt as u; So u = 3.
Define each Landmark District 's Peapod as J; So J = u = 3.
Define each Peapod 's Product as h; So h = u = 3.
Define each Landmark District 's Product as P; P = h * J = 3 * 3 = 9.
Define each High-rise Apartment Complex 's Metro (Canada) as g; So g = 13 * P = 13 * 9 = 2.
Define each High-rise Apartment Complex 's Peapod as S; So S = h - J = 3 - 3 = 0.
Define each High-rise Apartment Complex 's Supermarkets as v; So v = S + g = 0 + 2 = 2.
